item.dc:creator: @Weibs Weibs
item.description:
@Weibs wrote:

Cool, nice first script. Just got a suggestion, if you’re using moparscape, you could just use coordinates, but its good to get experience with bitmaps. Also, if you are going to use bitmaps, try to get small portions of what you’re looking for, not the whole thing. That will decrease lag a lot.

// Starts the script by clearing the debug and minimize SCAR.
Procedure StartScript;
Begin
// Clears the little panel right below the coding panel.
ClearDebug;

 // While i is above 0...
 i := 0;
 While (i > 0) do
 begin
      // Write this each time in the Status bar.
      Status('Script will start in ' + IntToStr(i) + ' second[s] and minimize itself.');

      // Decrease i by 1 each time.
      i := i-1;

      // Wait 1 second each time.
      Wait(1000);
 End;

 // Reverts Status bar back to what it was.
 Status('Running Script...');

 // Minimizes SCAR.
 GetApplication.MINIMIZE;

End;

// Procedure to Click on a bmp like this: ClickBmp(ff);
Procedure ClickBmp(bitmap:Integer);
Begin
// If it finds the bitmap then…
If(FindBitmap(bitmap, x, y))then
Begin
Wait(50+random(100));

      // Click on it.
      ClickMouse(x, y, true);
 End Else
 Begin
      // Displays error message.
      WriteLn('Could not find the bitmap ' + IntToStr(bitmap) + '.');

      // Terminates Script.
      TerminateScript;
 End;

End;

// Clicks the Play Now button.
Procedure ClickPlayNowButton;
Begin
If(FindBitmap(PlayNow, x, y))then
Begin
// Click on it.
ClickMouse(x, y, true);
End;
End;

// Types in Username, Password and Server Ip.
Procedure TypeInUsernamePasswordAndServerIp;
Begin

 // Types in Username.
 SendKeys(Username);
 Wait(100);

 // Presses Enter.
 SendKeys(Chr(13));
 
 // Types in Password.
 SendKeys(Password);
 Wait(100);
 
 // Presses Enter.
 SendKeys(Chr(13));

 // Types in Server Ip.
 SendKeys(ServerIp);
 Wait(100);

End;

// Logs into server.
Procedure LogOnToServer;
Begin
If(FindBitmap(Enter, x, y))then
Begin
// Click on it.
ClickMouse(x, y, true);
End;
End;

Begin
// Loads all the Bitmaps.
Load;

 // Starts the script and minimizes SCAR.
 StartScript;
 
 // Waits a little.
 Wait(200);
 
 // Goes to the log in screen.
 ClickPlayNowButton;
 
 // Waits a little.
 Wait(1000);

 // Types in Username, Password and Server Ip.
 TypeInUsernamePasswordAndServerIp;

 // Logs on to the server.
 LogOnToServer;

End.[/code]
